title.narrative: OUTPUT 3: PLANNING, MONITORING, REPORTING, GENDER AND PARTNERSHIPS

description.narrative: By 2022, programme planning, monitoring and reporting capacity and performance of government, UNICEF and sister UN agencies and CSOs are strengthened and gender-responsive for the improved delivery of results for children., which contributes to Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews, Evaluation, Private Sector Engagement, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Effectively plan, monitor, evaluate and report on programme delivery.

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF continued to provide the most needed and essential services to vulnerable children and women of Pakistan. With the successful launch and adaptation of the donor reporting portal; and the implementation of the revised fundraising strategy, the office mobilized US$233.60 million with 44new grants and effectively managed USD401.96 million ensuring programme and operational effectiveness of the multi programme year. With the current country programme ending in 2022, the office launched the process of developing a new programme of cooperation for 2023-2027. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:10/01/2022
